  "description": "Traditional tempering and slow simmering deepen the flavor so the meal tastes complete even with minimal oil. Avarakkai Paruppu Usili with Red Rice brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Steam or saute the vegetable with a splash of water on medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes until just tender.",
    "Heat oil in a kadai, add mustard and curry leaves, then add the crumbled steamed dal mixture and cook on medium-low heat for 4 minutes until dry and grainy.",
    "Fold in the cooked vegetable and cook 2 minutes more so the flavors combine.",
    "Serve the usili alongside or over the cooked grain as a composed lunch bowl."
  ],
